Where your project is novel

Based on these works, you can frame your contribution around:

Adaptive RL attacker vs. mostly heuristic or one‑shot methods

BAP uses CoT‑driven heuristic feedback loops for text adaptation 
1; there is little work that explicitly models the attacker as a Q‑learning agent with a state (history + CoT) and an action space of attack strategies.
Security surveys emphasise the rise of automated prompt attacks but primarily cover gradient‑based or search‑based universal triggers, not RL‑based multi‑turn strategies 
